TITLE: Registering a Gradle Task Using Avoidance API
DESCRIPTION: Example of using Gradle's task avoidance API to register a task lazily rather than creating it eagerly. This improves build configuration time by only executing configuration blocks when required.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/BUILDING.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: groovy
CODE:
```
tasks.register('someTask') { ... }
```

