TITLE: Using COUNT Function in Elasticsearch SQL
DESCRIPTION: The COUNT function returns the total number of input values. When used with a wildcard (*) or literal, all values are considered including null or missing ones. With a field name, null values are not counted.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/docs/reference/query-languages/sql/sql-functions-aggs.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
COUNT(expression) <1>
```

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT COUNT(*) AS count FROM emp;

     count
---------------
100
```

