TITLE: Truncating Dates and Times in SQL
DESCRIPTION: The DATE_TRUNC/DATETRUNC function truncates a date, datetime, or interval to the specified unit. It sets all fields less significant than the specified unit to zero (or one for day, day of week, and month).
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/docs/reference/query-languages/sql/sql-functions-datetime.md#2025-04-21_snippet_49

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
DATE_TRUNC(
    string_exp, <1>
    datetime_exp/interval_exp) <2>
```

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT DATE_TRUNC('millennium', '2019-09-04T11:22:33.123Z'::datetime) AS millennium;

      millennium
------------------------
2000-01-01T00:00:00.000Z
```

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT DATETRUNC('week', '2019-08-24T11:22:33.123Z'::datetime) AS week;

      week
------------------------
2019-08-19T00:00:00.000Z
```

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT DATE_TRUNC('centuries', INTERVAL '199-5' YEAR TO MONTH) AS centuries;

      centuries
------------------
 +100-0
```

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT DATE_TRUNC('days', INTERVAL '19 15:24:19' DAY TO SECONDS) AS day;

      day
------------------
+19 00:00:00
```

