TITLE: ESQL Ceiling Function Description
DESCRIPTION: Documentation note explaining the ceiling function behavior across different numeric types. For long and integer types it performs no operation, while for double values it finds the nearest double value to the integer similar to Java's Math.ceil function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/docs/reference/query-languages/esql/_snippets/functions/description/ceil.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: markdown
CODE:
```
% This is generated by ESQL's AbstractFunctionTestCase. Do no edit it. See ../README.md for how to regenerate it.

**Description**

Round a number up to the nearest integer.

::::{note}
This is a noop for `long` (including unsigned) and `integer`. For `double` this picks the closest `double` value to the integer similar to [Math.ceil](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/Math.html#ceil(double)).
::::
```

