TITLE: Parsing Datetime Strings in SQL
DESCRIPTION: The DATETIME_PARSE function parses a datetime string using a specified format pattern. It requires both date and time components and returns a datetime value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/docs/reference/query-languages/sql/sql-functions-datetime.md#2025-04-21_snippet_46

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
DATETIME_PARSE(
    string_exp, <1>
    string_exp) <2>
```

LANGUAGE: sql
CODE:
```
SELECT DATETIME_PARSE('07/04/2020 10:20:30.123', 'dd/MM/yyyy HH:mm:ss.SSS') AS "datetime";

      datetime
------------------------
2020-04-07T10:20:30.123Z
```

LANGUAGE: sql
