TITLE: Executing Boolean Field Script for Author Name Length
DESCRIPTION: This script uses the boolean_field context to check if an author's first name is between 1 and 4 characters long. It demonstrates string manipulation in Painless scripts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/docs/reference/scripting-languages/painless/painless-api-examples.md#2025-04-21_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: console
CODE:
```
POST /_scripts/painless/_execute
{
  "script": {
    "source": """
      int space = doc['author'].value.indexOf(' ');
      emit(space > 0 && space < 5);
    """
  },
  "context": "boolean_field",
  "context_setup": {
    "index": "my-index-000001",
    "document": {
      "name": "Dune",
      "author": "Frank Herbert",
      "release_date": "1965-06-01",
      "page_count": 604
    }
  }
}
```

