TITLE: Regex Explanation of CamelCase Tokenizer
DESCRIPTION: This regex explanation clarifies how the CamelCase tokenizer works.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/docs/reference/text-analysis/analysis-pattern-analyzer.md#2025-04-21_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: text
CODE:
```
  ([^\p{L}\d]+)                 # swallow non letters and numbers,
| (?<=\D)(?=\d)                 # or non-number followed by number,
| (?<=\d)(?=\D)                 # or number followed by non-number,
| (?<=[ \p{L} && [^\p{Lu}]])    # or lower case
  (?=\p{Lu})                    #   followed by upper case,
| (?<=\p{Lu})                   # or upper case
  (?=\p{Lu}                     #   followed by upper case
    [\p{L}&&[^\p{Lu}]]          #   then lower case
  )
```

