TITLE: Implementing KeyStoreWrapper Class in Java for Elasticsearch
DESCRIPTION: This class implements a wrapper for the KeyStore, providing methods for creating, loading, and saving key stores. It includes functionality for password-based encryption and handling of secure settings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/x-pack/plugin/security/licenses/accessors-smart-NOTICE.txt#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public class KeyStoreWrapper implements SecureSettings {
    private static final String KEYSTORE_TYPE = "PKCS12";
    private final KeyStore keyStore;
    private final char[] password;
    private final Path configPath;

    public KeyStoreWrapper(Path configPath, char[] password) throws Exception {
        this.configPath = configPath;
        this.password = password;
        keyStore = KeyStore.getInstance(KEYSTORE_TYPE);
        if (Files.exists(configPath)) {
            try (InputStream in = Files.newInputStream(configPath)) {
                keyStore.load(in, password);
            }
        } else {
            keyStore.load(null, password);
        }
    }

    // ... (other methods)

    @Override
    public void close() throws IOException {
        Arrays.fill(password, '\0');
    }
}
```

