TITLE: Implementing ExceptionsHelper Utility Class in Java
DESCRIPTION: Defines the ExceptionsHelper class with static utility methods for exception handling, including methods to extract root causes, unwrap exceptions, and generate detailed error messages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/modules/repository-azure/licenses/reactive-streams-NOTICE.txt#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public final class ExceptionsHelper {

    private ExceptionsHelper() {
    }

    public static RuntimeException convertToRuntime(Exception e) {
        if (e instanceof RuntimeException) {
            return (RuntimeException) e;
        }
        return new ElasticsearchException(e);
    }

    public static ElasticsearchException convertToElastic(Exception e) {
        if (e instanceof ElasticsearchException) {
            return (ElasticsearchException) e;
        }
        return new ElasticsearchException(e);
    }

    // ... (additional utility methods)

    public static String detailedMessage(Throwable t) {
        if (t == null) {
            return "Unknown";
        }
        if (t.getCause() == null) {
            return t.toString();
        }
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        while (t != null) {
            sb.append(t.toString()).append("; ");
            t = t.getCause();
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }

    // ... (additional methods)
}
```

