TITLE: Correct MongoDB Aggregation Pipeline Example
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows the correct way to use the current date in a MongoDB aggregation pipeline using aggregation variables.  It uses `$$NOW` to represent the current date, ensuring that the date is properly evaluated by MongoDB. An `$addFields` stage is used to create a `current_date` field, and `$expr` allows comparing fields.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/docs/reference/search-connectors/es-connectors-mongodb.md#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
{
  "aggregate": {
    "pipeline": [
      {
        "$addFields": {
          "current_date": {
            "$toDate": "$$NOW"
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "$match": {
          "$expr": {
            "$gte": [
              "$expiresAt",
              "$current_date"
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

