TITLE: Implementing StartupSelfCheck for Elasticsearch license validation in Java
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines the StartupSelfCheck class, which performs license-related checks during Elasticsearch startup. It verifies the license state and handles any issues encountered during the validation process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/x-pack/plugin/ql/licenses/antlr4-runtime-NOTICE.txt#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
class StartupSelfCheck implements Runnable {
    private final LicenseState licenseState;
    private final ThreadPool threadPool;

    StartupSelfCheck(LicenseState licenseState, ThreadPool threadPool) {
        this.licenseState = licenseState;
        this.threadPool = threadPool;
    }

    @Override
    public void run() {
        if (licenseState.isActive() == false) {
            threadPool.scheduleUnlessShuttingDown(TimeValue.timeValueSeconds(10L), ThreadPool.Names.GENERIC, this);
        }
    }
}
```

