TITLE: Defining ClusterCoordinateTopologyConfiguration Class in Java
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines the ClusterCoordinateTopologyConfiguration class, which extends ClusterCoordinateBaseConfiguration. It includes constructor, getter, and setter methods for managing cluster coordinate topology settings.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/modules/repository-gcs/licenses/google-oauth-client-NOTICE.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public class ClusterCoordinateTopologyConfiguration extends ClusterCoordinateBaseConfiguration {

    private final ClusterCoordinateSettings.TopologyImpl topology;

    public ClusterCoordinateTopologyConfiguration(
        ClusterCoordinateSettings.TopologyImpl topology,
        TimeValue publishTimeout,
        ClusterCoordinateSettings.Follower follower,
        int minimumMasterNodes,
        int expectedNodes,
        TimeValue initialClusterFormationWaitTime,
        NoMasterBlockService noMasterBlockService
    ) {
        super(publishTimeout, follower, minimumMasterNodes, expectedNodes, initialClusterFormationWaitTime, noMasterBlockService);
        this.topology = topology;
    }

    public ClusterCoordinateSettings.TopologyImpl getTopology() {
        return topology;
    }

    @Override
    public boolean equals(Object o) {
        if (this == o) return true;
        if (o == null || getClass() != o.getClass()) return false;
        if (super.equals(o) == false) return false;
        ClusterCoordinateTopologyConfiguration that = (ClusterCoordinateTopologyConfiguration) o;
        return Objects.equals(topology, that.topology);
    }

    @Override
    public int hashCode() {
        return Objects.hash(super.hashCode(), topology);
    }
}
```

