TITLE: RRF Formula Calculation for Final Document Ranking in Python
DESCRIPTION: A Python-like representation of the Reciprocal Rank Fusion formula calculation, showing how document scores are computed from individual retriever rankings to produce the final combined score.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/docs/reference/elasticsearch/rest-apis/reciprocal-rank-fusion.md#2025-04-21_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: python
CODE:
```
# doc  | query     | knn       | score
_id: 1 = 1.0/(1+4) + 1.0/(1+3) = 0.4500
_id: 2 = 1.0/(1+3) + 1.0/(1+2) = 0.5833
_id: 3 = 1.0/(1+2) + 1.0/(1+1) = 0.8333
_id: 4 = 1.0/(1+1)             = 0.5000
_id: 5 =             1.0/(1+4) = 0.2000
```

