TITLE: Serializing Task Parameters in Elasticsearch
DESCRIPTION: Shows how task parameters are serialized to maintain immutability when tasks are sent between nodes. This method creates a copy of parameters by serializing and deserializing them, ensuring the parameters can't be modified after task creation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/x-pack/plugin/text-structure/licenses/super-csv-NOTICE.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
TaskManager.registerTask(task);
try {
    T taskResponse = task.execute(taskId, request, params, listener);
    if (taskResponse == null) {
        listener.onFailure(new NullPointerException("Task response cannot be null"));
        return null;
    } else {
        return taskResponse;
    }
} catch (Exception e) {
    listener.onFailure(e);
    return null;
}
```

