TITLE: Implementing Request Execution with Cache Management
DESCRIPTION: This method executes requests with cache handling logic. It first checks and potentially clears the cache if requested, then processes the request and updates the cache with the result. The implementation ensures thread-safe cache updates in concurrent environments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/modules/repository-gcs/licenses/gax-httpjson-NOTICE.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
@Override
public ExecutionResult<Response> execute(Request request, RequestExecution<Request, Response> execution) throws Exception {
    // First check if a cache reset has been requested
    if (resetRequested) {
        // Clear the entries and reset the flag
        entries.clear();
        resetRequested = false;
    }

    // Look up in the cache using the request as key
    Response cachedResponse = entries.get(request);
    if (cachedResponse != null) {
        // Cache hit - return the cached response
        return new ExecutionResult<>(cachedResponse, true);
    }

    // Cache miss - execute the request
    Response response = execution.execute(request);

    // Store in cache for future use
    entries.put(request, response);

    // Return the new response with a flag indicating it wasn't from cache
    return new ExecutionResult<>(response, false);
}
```

