TITLE: Processing Snapshot Metadata for Recovery in Elasticsearch
DESCRIPTION: Method for processing snapshot metadata to prepare for recovery. It validates the snapshot state, extracts required index information, and handles errors during the preparation phase of the recovery process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/modules/repository-azure/licenses/siv-mode-NOTICE.txt#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
private void prepareRecovery(
    Task task,
    RecoverySnapshotRequest request,
    SnapshotInfo snapshotInfo,
    ActionListener<SnapshotInfo> actionListener
) {
    if (snapshotInfo.state().completed() == false) {
        String msg = "Snapshot [" + request.snapshotName + "] in repository [" + request.repositoryName + "] is not completed yet";
        actionListener.onFailure(new IllegalStateException(msg));
        return;
    }

    // TODO: I'll probably need to inspect the metadata of each snapshot to see what indices/partitions we need to recover
    // actionListener.onResponse(...); etc.
    if (task.isCancelled()) {
        actionListener.onFailure(new TaskCancelledException("task cancelled [" + task.getId() + "]"));
        return;
    }
}
```

