TITLE: Implementing Cache Reset Logic in Elasticsearch
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a method for resetting a cache that handles empty cache conditions. It uses a volatile field for thread visibility and provides a conditional reset mechanism based on the current thread's activity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/modules/repository-gcs/licenses/gax-httpjson-NOTICE.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
private volatile boolean resetRequested; // Flag to indicate if a reset has been requested

@Override
public void resetCache() {
    // Check if the cache is empty
    if (this.entries.isEmpty()) {
        // If empty, no need to reset - just clear the flag
        resetRequested = false;
        return;
    }
    // Otherwise, set flag to reset the cache later
    resetRequested = true;
}
```

