TITLE: Defining LicenseManager class for Elasticsearch license management in Java
DESCRIPTION: This snippet outlines the LicenseManager class, which handles license management operations in Elasticsearch. It includes methods for registering and unregistering license state listeners, as well as managing the license state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/x-pack/plugin/ql/licenses/antlr4-runtime-NOTICE.txt#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public class LicenseManager implements ClusterStateListener {
    private static final Logger logger = LogManager.getLogger(LicenseManager.class);

    private final Settings settings;
    private final ClusterService clusterService;
    private final LicenseState licenseState;
    private final StartupSelfCheck startupSelfCheck;

    private ScheduledExecutorService scheduler;

    public LicenseManager(Settings settings, ClusterService clusterService, ThreadPool threadPool) {
        this.settings = settings;
        this.clusterService = clusterService;
        this.licenseState = new LicenseState(() -> clusterService.state());
        this.startupSelfCheck = new StartupSelfCheck(licenseState, threadPool);
    }

    public void registerLicenseStateListener(LicenseStateListener listener) {
        licenseState.registerListener(listener);
    }

    public void unregisterLicenseStateListener(LicenseStateListener listener) {
        licenseState.unregisterListener(listener);
    }

    // ... more methods ...
}
```

