TITLE: Handling field name with dot notation in DotExpandingXContentParser
DESCRIPTION: This method converts field names containing dots (e.g., 'foo.bar') into nested object notation by creating a path structure when currentName() is called on the parser. It handles the special case where a field name begins with an underscore by preserving it.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/modules/ingest-attachment/src/test/resources/org/elasticsearch/ingest/attachment/test/sample-files/text-empty.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
@Override
public String currentName() throws IOException {
    String name = super.currentName();
    if (name != null && name.indexOf('.') > 0) {
        // If the field name starts with '_', we're in a metadata field and we leave the name as is
        if (name.charAt(0) == '_') {
            return name;
        }

        String path = XContentMapValues.dotNestedField(name, this.path);
        if (path != null) {
            return path;
        }
    }
    return name;
}
```

