TITLE: TestAccumulator Class Implementation in Java
DESCRIPTION: A utility class that accumulates test failures allowing tests to continue executing after encountering errors. It supports failure tracking, nested accumulators, and generating comprehensive error messages with details about all encountered failures.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/modules/repository-gcs/licenses/google-auth-NOTICE.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public class TestAccumulator implements AutoCloseable {
    private final List<String> errors = new ArrayList<>();
    private final TestAccumulator parent;
    private final String errorPrefix;

    public TestAccumulator() {
        this(null, "");
    }

    private TestAccumulator(TestAccumulator parent, String errorPrefix) {
        this.parent = parent;
        this.errorPrefix = errorPrefix;
    }

    /**
     * Creates a new accumulator that inherits from this one.
     */
    public TestAccumulator child(String prefix) {
        return new TestAccumulator(this, prefix);
    }

    /**
     * Adds a new error to the list of errors. Adds the {@link #errorPrefix},
     * if there is one.
     */
    public void error(String error) {
        errors.add(errorPrefix.isEmpty() ? error : errorPrefix + error);
    }

    /**
     * Does this accumulator or any of its ancestors contain any errors?
     */
    public boolean hasErrors() {
        return false == errors.isEmpty() || (null != parent && parent.hasErrors());
    }

    /**
     * Is this accumulator free of errors? What about its ancestors?
     */
    public boolean ok() {
        return false == hasErrors();
    }

    /**
     * The errors that this accumulator contains. Doesn't include errors from
     * the ancestors.
     */
    public List<String> errors() {
        return Collections.unmodifiableList(errors);
    }

    /**
     * Raises an {@link AssertionError} if there are any errors in this
     * accumulator or any of its ancestors. Otherwise this is a no-op.
     */
    @Override
    public void close() {
        if (ok()) {
            return;
        }
        if (null != parent) {
            errors().forEach(e -> parent.error(e));
            return;
        }
        throw new AssertionError("Accumulated errors:\n" + errors.stream().map(e -> "  " + e).collect(Collectors.joining("\n")));
    }
}
```

