TITLE: Handling license status responses in Elasticsearch using Java
DESCRIPTION: This method processes license status responses, determining if a license supports a specific feature. It handles both plain license responses and those with nested license information.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/modules/repository-gcs/licenses/gson-NOTICE.txt#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
@SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
public static Map<String, Object> getFeatureStatus(Map<String, Object> response, String feature) {
    if (response == null) {
        return null;
    }
    if (response.containsKey("license") == false) {
        return (Map<String, Object>) response.get(feature);
    }
    if (response.containsKey("features") == false) {
        return null;
    }
    Map<String, Object> features = (Map<String, Object>) response.get("features");
    return (Map<String, Object>) features.get(feature);
}
```

