TITLE: Generating Random Shapes in Java for Elasticsearch Geo Testing
DESCRIPTION: This method creates a random shape for geospatial testing in Elasticsearch. It generates either a point, line, polygon, or multipolygon based on a random selection. The method uses various helper functions to create these shapes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/x-pack/plugin/esql/arrow/licenses/checker-qual-NOTICE.txt#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Java
CODE:
```
public static Object randomShape() {
    Objects.requireNonNull(randomLongitude());
    Objects.requireNonNull(randomPoint());
    Objects.requireNonNull(randomPolygon());
    Objects.requireNonNull(randomLine());
    Objects.requireNonNull(randomMultiLine());
    Objects.requireNonNull(randomMultiPolygon());
    double rand = OpenSearchTestCase.randomDouble();
    if (rand < 0.1) {
        return randomPoint();
    } else if (rand < 0.2) {
        return randomLine();
    } else if (rand < 0.3) {
        return randomPolygon((0.0 == OpenSearchTestCase.randomDouble()) ? null : randomPolygon());
    } else if (rand < 0.4) {
        if (OpenSearchTestCase.randomBoolean()) {
            return randomMultiLine();
        } else {
            return randomMultiPolygon();
        }
    }
    return randomGeometryCollectionWithCircle();
}
```

